    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-07-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="237"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                <head>237. National Security Decision Memorandum 70<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d237fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1"
                            >Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> Files, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Institutional
                        Files, (H-Files), Box H-217, <gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss> Files,
                            <gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss> 70. Confidential. Copies were sent
                        to <persName corresp="#p_SGP1">Shultz</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_FPM1">Flanigan</persName>.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d237fn2">President <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> directed that cooperation with the
                        Soviet Union in space should be pursued, but that a direct approach to
                        Soviet Premier <persName corresp="#p_KAN1">Kosygin</persName> should not be
                        undertaken.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1970-07-10"
                        >July 10, 1970</date>.</dateline>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO:</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Director, National Aeronautics and Space Administration</item>
                    <item>The Director, Office of Science and Technology</item>
                    <item>The Executive Secretary, National Aeronautics and Space Council</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT:</head>
                    <item>International Space Cooperation: <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss>-<gloss
                            target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss> Activities</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has decided that space cooperation with the Soviet Union should be
                    pursued simultaneously through high-level. diplomatic and technical agency
                    channels. He has noted and approved the scope of a <gloss target="#t_US1"
                        >US</gloss>-<gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss> cooperative space. program
                    forwarded from the Ad Hoc Committee on International Space Cooperation through
                    the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Under Secretaries Committee.</p>
                <p>The President does not, at this time, desire to send a formal communication to
                    Premier <persName corresp="#p_KAN1">Kosygin</persName> urging closer space
                    cooperation. He will, however, consider such a message whenever it appears
                    likely that a concrete program proposal will be favorably received by the Soviet
                    Union.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
